    ```javascript
function closestFactors(num) {
    let factor1 = Math.floor(Math.sqrt(num + 2));
    while (true) {
        let factor2 = Math.floor((num + 2) / factor1);
        if (factor1 * factor2 === num + 2) {
            return [factor1, factor2];
        }
        factor2 = Math.floor((num + 1) / factor1);
        if (factor1 * factor2 === num + 1) {
            return [factor1, factor2];
        }
        factor1--;
    }
}
```

    1. Initialize factor1 as the square root of num + 2, rounded down to an integer.
2. In an infinite loop (which will eventually be broken), do the following:
3. Calculate factor2 as the integer division of (num + 2) by factor1. Check if the product of factor1 and factor2 equals num + 2; if so, return the pair (factor1, factor2).
4. Calculate factor2 as the integer division of (num + 1) by factor1. Check if the product of factor1 and factor2 equals num + 1; if so, return the pair (factor1, factor2).
5. If neither multiplication has produced num + 1 or num + 2, decrement factor1 and continue to the next iteration.
6. Since the loop will eventually find a valid pair of factors, this algorithm will always return a solution.

